column12: METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR COMMUNICATING A PREPAID CURRENCY CREDIT BALANCE TO A TELECOMMUNICATIONS DEVICE
column13: The method of communicating a currency credit balance to a telecommunications device (10) comprises the steps of registering the device with a node, such as a Mobile Service Center (20), querying a PrePaid Complex (50) by the node, a response (120) thereto to determine the prepaid currency credit balance, responding to the query with the actual prepaid currency credit balance in monetary units, and sending the balance information to the device (10). The method can not only be implemented upon registration of the device, but also during an ongoing call connection according to a preselected time interval, or at the termination of an ongoing call connection. The invention also includes a node (250) which enables communicating the prepaid currency credit balance to the telecommunications device (10), wherein the node includes a program module (260) adapted to query the prepaid complex (50) to determine the balance, receive a response from the complex which includes the balance, and send the balance to the device (10). The query, response, and sending of balance information can occur at the time the device (10) is registered, during an ongoing call connection according to a preselected time interval, or at the termination of an ongoing call connection.

column12: CLIP ARRANGEMENT FOR PORTABLE TELECOMMUNICATION INSTRUMENT
column13: A clip is disposed on the front portion of a portable telecommunication instrument in a spaced-overlying relationship with a sound transmission opening communicating with a speaker or microphone internally disposed in the instrument. The clip has an aperture extending through the clip and is aligned with the sound transmission opening. The clip may be integrally formed with the front portion of the instrument, or alternatively, detachably connected to the front portion of the instrument.

column12: METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR ADJUSTING THE pH OF A LIQUID.
column13: An electrochemical or electrodialytic method and apparatus (154) for producing liquid of a desired pH value from input liquid of a different pH value, or for adjusting the pH of an aqueous flowable fluid, entails an electrochemical mechanism for adjusting the pH of an aqueous flowable fluid and a mechanism for then electrochemically stabilizing the adjusted pH of the fluid. The apparatus (154) includes an inlet and a channel in fluid communication with the inlet. The channel has the appearance and properties of a U-shaped connected vessel. The U-shaped connected vessel includes an inlet accumulating passage in fluid communication with an active zone between two spaced electrodes wherein the active zone has a small volume relative to the passage for accelerating fluid flow from the passage through the active zone complying with the physics of connected vessels.

column12: Automated Inspection of Closed Package Contents and Scanning to Optically Coupled Systems
column13: Apparatus and associated methods relate to automatically generating a jurisdiction entry compliance indicator (JECI) based on an automatically generated content attributes profile (CAP) for a closed package. In an illustrative example, the CAP may be generated based on predetermined content attributes selected by a content characterization model as a function of a contents description profile (CDP) for the package. The CDP may, for example, be automatically generated by a natural language processing model as a function of a predetermined text description of contents of the package. The JECI may be generated as a function of the CAP, predetermined permissions rules, and predetermined permissions attributes. The predetermined permissions attributes may be associated with the originator. The predetermined permissions rules may be identified by a rules identification model as a function of the CAP and a destination of the package. Various embodiments may advantageously automatically inspect contents of closed packages.
column15: CARDENAS VICENTE;;TREVINO RAUL

column12: RECTANGULAR TANK FOR FUELS STORIMG.
column13: This invention refers to a tank for fuels storimg with floating inner roof to be used in service stations (gas stations) or distribution centrals. The problem is that presently, on service stations horizontal cylindrical-type storimg tanks exist and are installed, which are buried under earth, same that because of their design, construction and operation design, are constantly sending hydrocarbon vapors to atmosphere durimg their continuous activity. In essence, this invention consists on providing a storimg tank, totally different from the ones actually existing on market, since thank to its novel external and internal construction, which fulfills Pemex specifications and the main characteristic of which is the placement of a floating inner roof, same that avoids fuel evaporation and which also cooperates with environment "air" protection and thus people health.
column15: CARDENAS RAUL IGNACIO MENDOZA

column12: APPARATUS AND METHOD FOR ENHANCED CALLER IDENTIFICATION SERVICES
column13: A method and system (20) providing enhanced caller identification services when the identity of the calling party is not necessarily associated with a predetermined calling party telephone number. The system comprises a network node (60) including a program module (69) adapted to receive an identification code and a calling party telephone number; and a telephonic communication device (80) including a memory (85) with an index (250) wherein a first plurality of calling party telephone numbers are associated with a second plurality of calling party names according to a third plurality of personal identification codes. The communication device (80) includes a program module (87) adapted to receive the identification code and to search the index (250) for a selected calling party name corresponding to the identification code. The system (20) and method may also be implemented by using a network node (60) to maintain the index, and using the node (60) to search for a substituted calling party telephone number corresponding to the identification code. The substituted telephone number is then sent to the telephonic communication device (80) for display (or announcement) of a calling party name which corresponds to the substituted number according to an index in the device.
column15: GUTIERREZ VICTOR;;MONTOYA JESUS;;CARDENAS RAUL

column12: Sistema e processo para fornecer serviços de identificação de chamador
column13: "SISTEMA E PROCESSO PARA FORNECER SERVIçOS DE IDENTIFICAçãO DE CHAMADOR". Um processo e sistema (20) que fornece serviços aperfeiçoados de identificação de chamador quando a identidade da parte que chama não está necessariamente associada com um número telefónico de parte que chama predeterminado. O sistema compreende um nó de rede (60) que inclui um módulo de programa (69) adaptado para receber um código de identificação e um número de telefone de parte que chama; e um dispositivo de comunicação telefónica (80) que inclui uma memória (85) com um índice (250) no qual uma primeira pluralidade de números de telefone de parte que chama são associados com uma segunda pluralidade de nomes de parte que chama de acordo com uma terceira pluralidade de códigos de identificação pessoais. O dispositivo de comunicação (80) inclui um módulo de programa (87) adaptado para receber o código de identificação e para pesquisar o índice (250) para um nome de parte que chama selecionado que corresponde ao código de identificação. O sistema (20) e o processo podem também ser implementados utilizando um nó de rede (60) para manter o indice e utilizar o nó (60) para pesquisar um número de telefone de parte que chama substituído que corresponde ao código de identificação. O número de telefone substituido é então enviado para o dispositivo de comunicação telefónica (80) para exibição (ou anúncio) de um nome de parte que chama que corresponde ao número substituído de acordo com um índice no dispositivo.

column12: Processo e aparelho para ajustar o ph de um lìquido
column13: Patente de Invenção: <B>''PROCESSO E APARELHO PARA AJUSTAR O pH DE UM LìQUIDO''<D>. Processo eletroquímico ou eletrodialítico e aparelho para produzir um líquido de um valor de pH desejado a partir de um líquido de entrada de um valor de pH diferente, ou para ajustar o pH de um fluido fluente aquoso, onde se fazem necessários um mecanismo eletroquímico para ajustar o pH do fluido fluente aquoso e um mecanismo para a então estabilização eletroquímica do pH ajustado do fluido. O aparelho inclui uma entrada e um canal em comunicação de fluido com a entrada. O canal tem a aparência e propriedades de um recipiente conectado na forma U. O recipiente conectado na forma de U inclui uma passagem de acumulação em comunicação de fluido com uma zona ativa entre dois eletrodos espaçados, onde a zona ativa apresenta um volume pequeno com relação à passagem para acelerar o fluxo de fluido a partir da passagem através do zona ativa, de acordo com a física dos recipientes conectados.

column12: METHOD AND NETWORK FOR EMERGENCY CALL SERVICES
column13: A method and network provide mobile information for emergency calls based on mobile position during a call in progress. As soon as an Emergency Services Call is invoked, the Mobile Station position information is gathered using a Serving Entity. The position is then sent to an Anchor Entity [typically an Anchor Mobile Switching Center (AMSC) and Anchor Mobile Position Center (AMPC)] in communication with the Emergency Services Network (ESNE). After receiving the position information, the Anchor Entity makes the call setup to the ESNE, and the AMSC updates the AMPC. In one alternative embodiment, the Position Determining Entity determines the troubled and non-troubled locations and sends them to the ESNE. In a second alternative embodiment, only the troubled party location is sent to the ESNE as a result of the non-troubled party triggering a special key code during the request for the ESNE.
column15: SELENE LUGO SAUCEDO MARIA;;CARDENAS FLORES RAUL

column12: METHOD AND DEVICE FOR ELECTROCHEMICALLY DISINFECTING FLUIDS
column13: A method for treating fluids operates on a continuously flowing stream of fluid. The stream is acted upon in a continuous flow process to generate a disinfectant species (e.g., chlorine) in the stream and to simultaneously lower the pH of the stream below approximately 4.0. The stream is passed through and electrodialytic cell and an electric potential difference is applied across electrodes of the cell during the passage of the stream throu gh the cell. Relative to its flow through a channel upstream of the cell, the stream is accelerated when flowing through the cell. The stream at an outlet of the electrodialytic cell to raise the pH of the stream to a neutral range , thus producing a disinfected solution. This step may be implemented by passi ng the effluent stream between differentially charged electrodes, for example, of the same electrodialytic cell. A chemical disinfecting method is also disclosed.
column14: MOLOF ALAN H;;MIGNONE EDWARD J;;CARDENAS RAUL C

column12: COMPOSICIONES DE ASFALTO DE MEZCLA EN TIBIO COMO UN TRATAMIENTO DE LA SUPERFICIE DE PAVIMENTO
column13: Se describe en la presente un aditivo de asfalto de mezcla en tibio que comprende (a) una cera; (b) un ester fosforico, y (e) una amina grasa. De manera preferente el componente (a) es una cera de amida grasa y el componente (b) es un ester fosforico de alquilo C16-C18. Tambien se describe una composicion de aglutinante de asfalto de mezcla en tibio que comprende asfalto y un aditivo de asfalto de mezcla en tibio, y metodos para su preparacion de los mismos. Se describe adicionalmente una composicion de asfalto de mezcla en tibio que comprende un aglutinante de asfalto de mezcla en tibio y un agregado, y metodos para la preparacion de los mismos.

column12: WARM MIX ASPHALT COMPOSITIONS AS A PAVEMENT SURFACE TREATMENT
column13: Disclosed herein is a warm mix asphalt additive comprising (a) a wax; (b) a phosphoric ester; and (c) a fatty amine. Preferably component (a) is a fatty amide wax and component (b) is a C16-C18 alkyl phosphoric ester. Also disclosed is a warm mix asphalt binder composition comprising asphalt and a warm mix asphalt additive, and methods for its preparation thereof. Additionally disclosed is a warm mix asphalt composition comprising a warm mix asphalt binder and aggregate, and methods for its preparation thereof.

column12: SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR BATTERY SELECTION
column13: Disclosed is a vehicle comprising a vehicle system having a system having a number of loads defining a load profile; a validated battery comprising one or more batteries which can fulfill the load profile; an integrated battery selected from the validated battery, the integrated battery selected for longevity relative to other batteries; wherein the validated battery is provided within the vehicle. column12: ELECTRONIC MONITOR FOR HEALTH THROUGH CLOTHING ITEMS.
column13: The present disclosure is related to a wearable electronic device for monitoring clinical variables of one or more users under observation through body wireless technology as a bridge to communicate clinical variables of a person directly from his body to a database which stores temperature behavior, fall detection, electrocardiogram and geographical location in a controlled or uncontrolled environment; which may be accessed through a mobile or web interface directly in the controlled environment or on the Internet. This invention includes a modified t-shirt on both the front and rear sides thereof with an elastic band which is innerly woven into the t-shirt so as to surround the top of the rib cage and clinical sensors of a conductive fabric which have communication lines woven into the elastic band and the t-shirt, allowing communication with a controller device. Said controller comprises a processing module referred to as "SoC", a navigation module, an input and output module refe rred to as "I/O", a wireless communication module, a nonvolatile storage module referred to as "memory" and a set of communication channels between the synchronous/asynchronous modules. This invention also includes a method to detect a critical fall and not a false alarm, such as an abrupt movement, a jump etc.

column12: SEED-GERMINATION AND SEEDLING-ELONGATION STIMULANT BASED ON LARREA TRIDENTATA EXTRACTS.
column13: The present invention refers to the use of water-soluble extracts of Larrea as promoters for the germination of seeds and the elongation of epicotyls and ridicles, and increasing the dry biomass in seedlings of diverse agricultural crops. The invention includes and describes a method for applying bioproducts, which is based on soaking the seeds in aqueous solutions of Larrea tridentata extracts for a predetermined period of time before setting the same under suitable conditions for the germination thereof and the development of the seedling. The Larrea tridentata extracts may be available in water-soluble powders or a liquid solution, which may be used alone, mixed together, or with diverse agrochemical products, such as growth regulators, pesticides, fertilizers or nutrients. The mixtures may be useful for preparing aqueous solutions at different concentrations, which depends on the type of seed and the desired results.

column12: Apparatus for the treatment of wastewater sludge
column13: According to an embodiment thereof, the apparatus comprises a pair of reaction vessels in which, sequentially, to treat the sludge. Both vessels are pressurized, and the first thereof has an aerator for aerating the sludge, and receives sulfuric acid and chlorine thereinto through a port. A dewatering device is provided upstream of the first vessel, and the outlet of the first vessel is coupled to an inlet of the second vessel through another dewatering device. The second vessel defines a final-treatment chamber in which the sludge is exposed to ozone, air and lime. The treatment method, then, comprises the steps carried out in the apparatus, namely: introducing the sludge into the first vessel and oxidizing and depressing the pH of the sludge so introduced, and recycling the sludge in the first vessel over a given period of time. Thereafter the sludge is dewatered and conducted to the second vessel wherein it is exposed to air, ozone and lime, as aforesaid, and discharged after a like period of time. The solid and liquid constituents are separated from the discharged sludge, and the latter is returned to the first vessel.

column12: Method for the treatment of wastewater sludge
column13: According to an embodiment thereof, the method comprises using a pair of reaction vessels, sequentially, to treat the sludge. Both vessels are pressurized, and the first thereof has an aerator for aerating the sludge, and receives sulfuric acid and chlorine thereinto through a port. A dewatering device is provided upstream of the first vessel, and the outlet of the first vessel is coupled to an inlet of the second vessel through another dewatering device. The second vessel defines a final-treatment chamber in which the sludge is exposed to ozone, air and lime. The treatment method, then, comprises the steps namely: introducing the sludge into the first vessel and oxidizing and depressing the pH of the sludge so introduced, and recycling the sludge in the first vessel over a given period of time. Thereafter the sludge is dewatered and conducted to the second vessel wherein it is exposed to air, ozone and lime, as aforesaid, and discharged after a like period of time. The solid and liquid constituents are separated from the discharged sludge, and the latter is returned to the first vessel.

column13: SE REFIERE A UN MODULO DE DESTILACION QUE INCORPORA DISPOSITIVOS MECANICOS, ELECTRICOS Y ELECTRONICOS QUE PERMITAN LLEVAR A CABO EL REGISTRO Y CONTROL DE VARIABLES TALES COMO LA TEMPERATURA, TIEMPO Y GRADO ALCOHOLICO, DURANTE EL PROCESO DE DESTILACION, OPTIMIZANDO LA SEPARACION DE LAS FRACCIONES. DICHO MODULO ESTA CONFORMADO POR: UNA UNIDAD DE CALOR; UN TANQUE ENCHAQUETADO PARA FLUIDO DE CALENTAMIENTO DE MOSTO; UN CUELLO DE CISNE; UN TANQUE DE ENFRIAMIENTO DE VAPORES; UNA UNIDAD DE SEPARACION DE FRACCIONES: CABEZA, CUERPO Y COLA; UNA UNIDAD DE REGISTRO CONTINUO DE GRADO ALCOHOLICO EN DICHAS FRACCIONES; UNA UNIDAD DE CONTROL Y AUTOMATIZACION PARA LA TEMPERATURA; UN SISTEMA DE AUTOMATIZACION CONFORMADA POR UNA UNIDAD DE CONTROL DE TEMPERATURA, GRADO ALCOHOLICO Y MECANISMO DE SEPARACION DE FRACCIONES, UTILIZANDO PARA ELLO UN SOFTWARE QUE CONTROLA EL FUNCIONAMIENTO DE TODO EL SISTEMA

column12: DIMMABLE HIGH INTENSITY LEDS LUMINAIRE WITH EMERGENCY BALLAST FOR PARKING AREAS.
column13: A high intensity dimmable LEDs luminaire with emergency ballast for car parks for use with fixed or dimmable output comprising a semi-concave shell, characterized in that it has a passage at the center of the skeleton having an inverted "U" shape to accommodate an AC current source, emergency ballast, a set of batteries and electrical harness and in that it has at its concave side ends, a plurality of PCB or MCPBC card and metal heat dissipating elements.

column12: SYSTEM AND METHOD OF AUTOMATED DATA ANALYSIS FOR GENERATING SENSING OBJECTS.
column13: The present invention is a system capable of identifying patterns for the generation of sensing metrics or analytics based on an automated analysis method for large amount of data. The system comprise one start parameter initialization module, one data source module, one data extractor module, one raw data warehouse, one indexer module, one data processor module, one sensing object gathering module, one sensing object lookup module, four one-way communication channels and three bi-directional communication channels.

column12: DETERMINADOR DE GRADO ALCOHOLICO EN LINEA
column13: MEDIANTE UN SISTEMA QUE GARANTIZA UN FLUJO ESTABLE DE LA SUSTANCIA DE LA CUAL SE QUIERE MEDIR SU CONTENIDO DE GRADO ALCOHOLICO, Y QUE COMPRENDE: a)UN SENSOR DE FLEXION, PARA LA DETECCION DE LAS VARIACIONES DE DENSIDAD; Y, b) UN SISTEMA ELECTRONICO FORMADO POR: i) UN SISTEMA DE ACONDICIONAMIENTO QUE AMPLIFICA LA SENAL PROVENIENTE DE (a) POR MEDIO DE UNA CONFIGURACION DE AMPLIFICADORES OPERACIONALES E IMPEDANCIAS; Y, ii) UNA ETAPA DE CONTROL FORMADA POR UN MICROCONTROLADOR (Pic 16F877) LA CUAL TIENE ALMACENADA EN SU MEMORIA UN PROGRAMA DE CONTROL QUE REGISTRA Y PROCESA LA SENAL PROVENIENTE DE (i) Y LA CONVIERTE EN INFORMACION LA CUAL ES MOSTRADA EN UNA PANTALLA LCD. EL SISTEMA MIDE LA VARIACION DE LA RESISTENCIA ELECTRICA EN (a), LA CUAL GENERA UNA VARIACION DE VOLTAJE QUE ES REGISTRADA Y PROCESADA EN (b) Y CUYA SENAL DE SALIDA ES MOSTRADA EN (c) COMO UN VALOR DEL GRADO ALCOHOLICO DE LA SUSTANCIA

column12: SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR DETECTING TRAFFIC JAMS AND CONTAMINATING SUBSTANCES.
column13: The present disclosure is related to a system and method that is capable of identifying patterns that allow traffic jams and contamination detection, based on an automated analysis method involving large volumes of data. The traffic jam and contamination detection system is characterized by comprising at least one initializing module for start-up parameters, at least one data reception module, at least one data storage module, at least one contamination detection module, at least one location and speed detection module, at least 7 bidirectional communication channels and at least one unidirectional communication channel.

column12: ARBOL NAVIDENOS FUNCIONAL PARA ESPACIOS REDUCIDOS
column13: El arbol navideno funcional para espacios reducidos es una propuesta innovadora que soluciona el problema de ubicacion de arboles en areas reducidas, lo que da mayor seguridad en la amplitud de area para evacuar en casos de sismos, es funcional por que se adapta a espacios reducidos, es liviano, facil de armar y desmontar, no ocupa espacios para su almacen porque es plegable, no posee aristas cortantes ideal para armarlo en familia, se adapta a la eleccion del color y la decoracion del cliente

column12: PLASTIC BIOFIBER BASED ON NUTSHELLS AND POLYURETHANE, METHOD OF OBTAINING AND USING THE SAME.
column13: The present invention describes a plastic biofiber based on nutshells and polyurethane, the method of obtaining and using the same; said invention is a material that contains natural fiber mainly obtained from the cellulose of nut, so that having better physical and chemical qualities, an improved finish, which is similar to that of wood, a suitable stiffness and being environmentally friendly, the invention may help to the use and reuse of the largest pollutant of the earth , which is polyurethane, the nutshell having qualities of activated coal, since inhibits the toxic characteristics of the reactions of polyurethane with the organic solution.
